<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                    <head>No. 425.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bingham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 22,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 576.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                        dispatch No. 1250 of the 7th ultimo, and to approve your action reported
                        therein, in respect of the order amending the consular court regulations as
                        to the punishment for crimes and offenses against the laws of the United
                        States.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>